{"id":950,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":950,"title":"Pekah","subtitle":"","short_title":"Pekah","uri":"/scriptures/bd/pekah","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/pekah.t1","order":".000.2615"},[".title","Pekah"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/pekah.p1","order":".000.2616"},["i","Open-eyed."],"Son of Remaliah; kills his master Pekahiah and becomes king of Israel (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/15.25-32"},"2 Kgs. 15:25–32"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/16.1"},"16:1"],"); invades Judah with Rezin (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/15.37"},"2 Kgs. 15:37"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/16.5"},"16:5"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/28.6"},"2 Chr. 28:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/7.1"},"Isa. 7:1"],"); Israel invaded by Tiglath-pileser; Pekah killed by Hoshea (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/15.29-30"},"2 Kgs. 15:29–30"],"). There is much difficulty in deciding the chronology of Pekah’s reign. See",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bible-chron"},"Bible Chronology"],"in the appendix."]]],"refs":null}
